'''Do it for Denmark''' is a [[Denmark|Danish]] media and advertising campaign designed to increase the [[birth rate]] of the nation. The campaign, launched by the Danish travel agency [[Spies Rejser]], is envisioned as a way to stop the [[population decline]] present in Denmark. Following the implementation of the campaign in 2014, the Danish birth rate increased.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2014/03/27/do-it-for-denmark-campaign-wants-danes-to-have-more-sex-a-lot-more-sex/|title=‘Do it for Denmark!’ campaign wants Danes to have more sex. A lot more sex.|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=3 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.spies.dk/do-it-for-denmark|title=Do it for Denmark|website=www.spies.dk|access-date=2016-12-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/denmark-s-bizarre-series-of-sex-campaigns-lead-to-baby-boom-a7062466.html|title=Denmark is fighting its low birth rate in the creepiest way possible|date=2016-06-02|newspaper=The Independent|language=en-GB|access-date=2016-12-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.rt.com/news/345499-denmark-baby-boom-sex/|title=‘Screw for Denmark’ sex campaigns produce baby boom in months|newspaper=RT International|language=en-EN|access-date=2016-12-04}}</ref>

